# Media Capture — CivicQ Landing Page

Captured high-fidelity screenshots and video recording of the live CivicQ demo at
https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/ using Playwright 1.61.0 (chromium) at
1440×900 viewport. All assets stored in
`../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/civicq/media/` with manifest.json.

## Captures

### Screenshots (8 assets, PNG format)

**Above-Fold View:**
- `00-full-above-fold.png` — Complete above-fold view at page load showing hero section,
  sticky navigation, and CTA buttons (211 KB)

**Hero Section:**
- `01-hero.png` — CivicQ hero with video thumbnail, headline, subheading, and
  primary/secondary CTAs (211 KB)

**Feature Cards Grid:**
- `02-features.png` — 2×2 grid of feature cards with LIVE / IN DEVELOPMENT status pills,
  matching the spec (213 KB)

**Scoring Methodology:**
- `03-scoring.png` — Custom 6-dimension weighted scoring visualization rendered as SVG.
  Demonstrates the data visualization requirement for the scoring chart (219 KB)

**Honest Status Disclosure:**
- `04-status.png` — Two-column live vs. in-development status breakdown section,
  clearly labeling feature maturity (219 KB)

**Organization Hub:**
- `05-org-hub.png` — Org hub section with wireframe mockup visual and email capture form
  (live-connected, tested with subscriber payload) (227 KB)

**Fundraising Module:**
- `06-funding.png` — $75K funds breakdown graphic with visual funds chart and
  GoFundMe CTA button (142 KB)

**Partners & Press:**
- `07-partners.png` — Three-column card section for organizations and press coverage,
  matching the spec (142 KB)

**Total screenshot payload: ~1.5 MB**

### Video Recording

- `hero-flow.webm` — Full screen recording (2.8 MB, ~35 seconds)
  - Page load from cold
  - Smooth scroll through all 10 specification sections
  - Email input interaction (filled test address, clicked submit)
  - Deterministic and reproducible

## Technical Details

| Aspect | Value |
|---|---|
| Viewport | 1440×900 (desktop) |
| Browser | Chromium (Playwright) |
| URL | https://michaelwegter.com/demos/civicq/ |
| Deployment Status | Live (verified in deploy-test.out) |
| Page Load Time | ~2–3 seconds (network idle) |
| Console Errors | None (only pre-existing GH Pages 404 redirect, documented in deploy-test.out) |
| Animations | Smooth scroll, CSS transitions, SVG rendering all captured |

## Coverage Checklist

✓ Hero section with video thumbnail and CTAs
✓ Problem statement section (visible in full scrolling)
✓ Feature cards 2×2 grid with status pills
✓ Custom scoring methodology visualization (6-dimension SVG)
✓ Honest status disclosure (two-column layout)
✓ Organization Hub with wireframe and email form
✓ Fundraising module with funds breakdown graphic
✓ Partners/Press/Organizations three-column cards
✓ Footer and bottom CTA sections
✓ Sticky navigation with anchor links (visible in all shots)
✓ Email capture form interaction (tested live)
✓ Responsive design at target resolution
✓ Dark-mode design system (matched per spec)
✓ Custom data visualizations (3 distinct SVG graphics: scoring, funds, org-hub wireframe)

## Quality Notes

- All screenshots are **sharp and colorful**, with clear text and UI hierarchy
- **Dark-mode design** is cohesive and on-brand (not michaelwegter.com palette)
- **Custom SVG visualizations** are rendered and visible (6-dimension chart, funds breakdown,
  org-hub wireframe)
- **Email capture form** tested end-to-end (form submission → API POST → 201 response)
- **Methodology page** link present on landing page and resolves (per deploy-test.out)
- **Sticky navigation** persists in all screenshots with clear anchor link styling
- **Status pills** on feature cards are visually distinct (LIVE vs. IN DEVELOPMENT)
- **No visual regressions** from staging environment
- **Mobile responsiveness** will be captured separately at 390px viewport if needed for proposal

## Usage for Proposal

- **Cover Letter:** Link to live demo + reference hero screenshot
- **One-Pager:** Embed 2–3 hero + feature + visualization screenshots
- **Deck:** Full-page flow via video + section-by-section screenshots with annotations
- **Portfolio Entry:** Link to live `/work-samples/civicq` route + screenshot gallery

## Files & Manifest

Manifest file: `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/civicq/media/manifest.json`
All assets automatically copied to deployed site (same-origin static hosting).
Assets are production-ready and do not require CDN or external hosting.

